<br>
characters doing the Thurgadin Prayer Shawl quests need to bake, at the least (prob need pottery or smithing too, but that can be another posting)<br>
<br>
East Freeport, and other places, sell a Cooking Spit.  your own portable oven<br>
<br>
East Commons - westernmost area has a single hut with an erudite vendor   Batwings (good to know anyway)<br>
<br>
First inn in east commons has a vendor in one of the outlying bldgs, and he sells Sauce and Frosting<br>
<br>
East Freeport Port Authority sells fish<br>
<br>
1. get the spit<br>
2. buy a bunch of batwings and frosting<br>
3. spit those til you are at 46 skill<br>
<br>
4. get fish and sauce<br>
5. spit those til skill is 82<br>
<br>
6. fish and batwings<br>
7  spit til 135<br>
<br>
(if i read right, about 130 is what we need for the shawl quest baking)<br>
<br>
total cost to me, today, to go from 22 skill to 132, was 18 PP and change.  By the time we get to the shawl quests, 18PP is pretty easy to come by.  Took me about 2 hours total, with unremarkable intelligence of low 80s<br>
<br>
