<br>
Here is what I have found on the Shawl quests! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Turn in 4 Frost Giant toes to Loremaster Borannin in the Cleric's Guild. These are found in GD and EW.<br>
<br>
<br>
Loremaster Borannin starts this quest by giving you a 10 slot box. Put a Frost Giant head in each slot, <br>
and press combine. Return the box, along with your first shawl for the second shawl. Frost Giants are found in EW and GD. <br>
<br>
<br>
This quest involves Mordin (love that B5 reference, but he should have had the head quest) in the meat shop. <br>
He is going to ask you to do some cooking. <br>
He gives you a napkin, and you must make a Tundrabear Sandwich. (Non Stackable) Tundra Kodiak Meat + sauce in oven.<br>
Add this to a loaf of bread in a mixing bowl. This should make a sandwich. Take this and the napkin to Guard Lief, <br>
outside the Paladin's Guild, and he will give you a used napkin. Tundra Kodiaks in GD and EW. <br>
<br>
2 Snow Bunny Meat + Sauce in a mixing bowl (Lost bowl I think). Result + spice + water (2) + pot in oven. <br>
(I know I lost the pot) Bunnies in EW. Trita Coldheart is across from the Fur and Leather shop, in the back along with the napkin. <br>
<br>
2 Ulthork meats (stackable) + vinegar + spice in bowl. Result + dough + pie tin in oven (Pie tin evaporates). <br>
Give the Ulthork Meat Pie to Loremaster Brita in the back right of the Cleric's Guild along with the napkin. <br>
<br>
<br>
Snow Griffin Souffle is hard in that you must get 4, no drop, snow griffin eggs. These are combined with spice in the oven. <br>
This is taken to the Grandmaster Thoridain in the Cleric's Guild.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Create a Velium Vial by putting a small brick of Velium, 3 crystalline silks, and 2 glass shards in the pottery wheel. <br>
Then fire the result using a high quality firing sheet in the kiln. Get the Velium Purifier from Frundle Frenkler. Put the vial <br>
you have made, and 2 small pieces of Velium in the purifier and hit combine. This makes a gate potion for Thurgadin. <br>
(You can use this also.) Give the potion to Tanik Greskil in the snow near the Entrance to Kael. You may spawn the Death Squad <br>
trying to get him to appear. Then the note he gives you and your shawl are turned in. (everything drops in CC... some also drop elsewhere)<br>
<br>
<br>
Combine 5 crystalline silk threads and a glowing shardwurm bile in the bile extractor from Rexx Frostweaver to create <br>
glowing crystalline silk. (Do this five times). You will have to combine 5 of these created threads, and combine them with <br>
your shawl in a sewing kit. The crystalline silk threads drop in Velk's Lab. The shardwurm bile is off of shardwurms in GD.<br>
<br>
<br>
Betti Frostreaver will be your guide on this quest. She will give you a pattern to use. Combine a Woven Giant's Beard, 2 <br>
Manticore Manes, 2 Drakel Wolf Whiskers, and 2 Siren Hairs in a sewing kit (It may have to be the Coldain Tanner's kit)to make a <br>
thread. Put your shawl, the thread, and the pattern in the kit, PRAY, and hit combine. <br>
<br>
<br>
Start out by showing your 6th shawl to Betti Frostweaver in the Thurgadin Exchange. Betti Frostweaver says 'Spectacular artistry! <br>
I doubt I could have done better myself. You'll have to forgive me, I know time is short and I tend to carry on. This is the pattern <br>
for the making of a rune sacred to our people. It will be our final test of your craftsmanship and will put many of your skills to the <br>
test, but I trust you'll find the finished product to be more than worth the effort. Show Gilthan the silk shawl, he will set you on the <br>
path. May Brell always be with you outlander. Now show your shawl to Gilthan. And here we go:<br>
<br>
Combine a Runed Seashell (with charge of enduring breath) from the Sirens in Cobalt Scar with a small brick of velium in a mortar and pestle <br>
to make enchanted Velium Powder. (Pottery trivial at 18<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Combine the powder and a water on the pottery wheel to make an Unfired Rune. (Pottery Trivial at 18<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Fire the rune with a High Quality Firing Sheet AND A WATER to make a Blank Rune. (Pottery Trivial at 18<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Show the Rune to Trademaster Kroven in the Exchange who will give you a Prayer to Brell. Wander about the lecture hall <br>
saying this prayer over and over until you get inspired. You will find an Etched Rune Pattern on the floor in front of you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Combine an Ulthork Tusk, an Ulthork Hide, and a Swordfish Tooth in a fletching kit to make a burin. (Fletching trivial at ?)<br>
<br>
<br>
